title: Ostrich attempts to break into CAR at English safari park with its beak
text:
12 shares
View
comments
A cheeky ostrich attempted to gain access to a car by pecking at the door handle with its beak.
The humorous and rather surprising footage was captured at a safari park in England, although it's not clear which one.
In the 15-second clip the angry ostrich is filmed by the passenger via the side mirror of a car.
Grand Theft Ostrich! Feathered foe attempts to hijack car The angry ostrich was filmed by the passenger via the side mirror of a car attempting to break in with its beak
The video shows the bird appearing in the frame and immediately slamming its head against the vehicle's door.
Remarkably, the ostrich seems to know to go for the handle and has four attempts at trying to latch onto it with its beak.

Travel enthusiast captures rare footage of striated... 12 shares It is unsuccessful however as each time it tries to get a grip of the handle it finds that it is unable to keep it in its beak.
The break-in attempt finishes with the big bird giving up and straightening up alongside the car.
The big bird glared at the people in the car after giving up its attempts to break into it at a safari park in England
The bird slammed its head against the handle four times and the driver later said that it had scratched the door
The video maker then films it from the passenger window and captures it glaring at the couple before pecking the ground.
The clip concludes with the couple continuing through the safari park and the driver saying: ‘Grand Theft Ostrich’.
Writing online after posting the video to YouTube, the owner of the car said that the bird had scratched the door with its beak during the break-in attempt.
